main event: A witness observed a luminous unidentified aerial phenomenon in Austin, Texas on January 6, 1953.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be approximately 500 to 700 miles per hour in speed.,The object was described as being approximately 25 to 50 feet in diameter.,The object had a bluish-white color.,The witness was considered reliable by the investigator.,No explanation was provided for the phenomenon observed.
